company_description: Mayson is a zero vendor lock-in Backend-as-a-Service (BaaS) platform that helps developers, startups, and enterprises build backends faster, smarter, and without restrictions. With Mayson, you can use AI-powered prompts to generate complete backends or new API endpoints — the system automatically designs the database schema, links related tables, and creates production-ready APIs. Unlike traditional BaaS platforms, Mayson gives you full ownership of your code: you can download it, customize it with Python (Node.js and Go coming soon), and deploy it anywhere — your own cloud, on-premise, or Mayson’s managed infrastructure. In short, Mayson combines the speed of low-code, the flexibility of custom code, and the freedom of no vendor lock-in.

company_description: TimeTeller is a spin-off from Charité – Universitätsmedizin Berlin, leveraging circadian biology to optimize the timing of cancer treatments. Using a simple, saliva test, we generate a personalized profile of each patient’s internal biological clock to align therapy with their optimal treatment window. This approach can significantly reduce side effects and enhance efficacy and is already being validated in clinical studies at over 10 hospitals. Our patent-protected technology is built on cutting-edge research in oncology and chronobiology. Our goal: to revolutionize cancer care by making treatment not only more effective, but also more humane. Our current focus is oncology, because, every year, more than 19 million people worldwide are diagnosed with cancer. But our potential extends far beyond that. We have studies in Parkinson’s, women’s health, sports, and longevity. We want to become a global player in cancer therapy and personalized medicine with a European innovation.

company_description:
At Altum Sequencing we revolutionize cancer monitoring after diagnosis and treatment. Using cutting-edge DNA sequencing, we can detect a single tumor cell among a million healthy ones—from just a simple blood sample.

While traditional imaging techniques can miss up to 40% of cases, our technology enables doctors to make faster decisions in real time, reduce healthcare costs and avoid invasive procedures for patients.

We empower doctors to personalize treatment: intensifying it when residual disease remains or reducing it when it’s safe—minimizing side effects and maximizing outcomes.

Our mission is to give every cancer patient the precise, tailored care they deserve.
